"title": "4690: wings",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4690: wings",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Limbs which enable flight. In Scripture these are mainly used either of angelic beings or in various symbolic senses, especially of God's protection.</p>\n<h2>Wings of birds or insects</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:14\">GEN 7:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:17\">LEV 1:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:13\">JOB 39:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:26\">JOB 39:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa18:1\">ISA 18:1</a></p>\n<h3>Clean and unclean winged creatures</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:13-Lev11:25\">LEV 11:13–11:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:11-Deut14:20\">DEU 14:11–14:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:12-Acts10:15\">ACT 10:12–10:15</a></p>\n<h2>Wings of angelic beings</h2>\n<h3>Cherubim</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:20\">EXO 25:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:9\">EXO 37:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:6-1Kgs8:7\">1KI 8:6–8:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:7-2Chr5:8\">2CH 5:7–5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:18\">1CH 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:11-2Chr3:13\">2CH 3:11–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:5-Ezek1:25\">EZK 1:5–1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:13\">EZK 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek10:5-Ezek10:22\">EZK 10:5–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>Other angelic beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:2\">ISA 6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:6\">ISA 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:8\">REV 4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Wings as a metaphor of protection</h2>\n<h3>Birds protect their young</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:11\">DEU 32:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:15\">ISA 34:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:37\">MAT 23:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34\">LUK 13:34</a></p>\n<h3>God's protection likened to a bird's wings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:4\">EXO 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:12\">RUT 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:8\">PSA 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps36:7\">PSA 36:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:1\">PSA 57:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps61:4\">PSA 61:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:7\">PSA 63:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:5\">ISA 31:5</a></p>\n<h3>Egypt's protection likened to an eagle's wings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:7\">EZK 17:7</a> <em>Zedekiah's fruitless appeal to Egypt for help against Babylon</em></p>\n<h2>Wings as a metaphor for God's judgment</h2>\n<h3>Judgment on Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:49\">DEU 28:49</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:7-Isa8:8\">ISA 8:7–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:3-Ezek17:4\">EZK 17:3–17:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos8:1\">HOS 8:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:8\">HAB 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech5:9\">ZEC 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>Judgment on others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:40\">JER 48:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:22\">JER 49:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:9\">REV 9:9</a></p>\n<h2>Other figurative uses of wings</h2>\n<h3>God rides on the wings of the wind</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:11\">2SA 22:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:10\">PSA 18:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:3\">PSA 104:3</a></p>\n<h3>God renews his people's strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:31\">ISA 40:31</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Israel described as a winged bird</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:13\">PSA 68:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:14\">ISA 10:14</a></p>\n<h3>Wings symbolise the ability to escape</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:6\">PSA 55:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:14\">REV 12:14</a></p>\n<h3>Wings symbolise instability</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:5\">PRO 23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:20\">ECC 10:20</a></p>\n<h3>Wings symbolise strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:6\">DAN 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:4\">DAN 7:4</a></p>\n<h3>Wings of the dawn</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:9\">PSA 139:9</a></p>\n<h3>Wings of the sun</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:2\">MAL 4:2</a> <em>God is likened to the rays of the sun.</em></p>",
